1
00:00:27,527 --> 00:00:30,948
THE HUSBAND

2
00:00:35,202 --> 00:00:36,410
THIS SERIES IS FICTITIOUS

3
00:00:36,411 --> 00:00:39,039
CHILDREN WERE FILMED SAFELY
GEN AI WAS USED IN SELECT SCENES

4
00:00:39,540 --> 00:00:41,707
WOORI TOGETHER MEDICAL CENTER

5
00:00:41,708 --> 00:00:42,709
Dr. Kang.

6
00:00:44,920 --> 00:00:46,046
I mean, Taeju.

7
00:00:51,009 --> 00:00:52,511
Are you really going to…

8
00:00:55,639 --> 00:00:56,765
end things with Seyun?

9
00:01:01,353 --> 00:01:02,896
I don't know…

10
00:01:05,232 --> 00:01:06,900
…if I can do this anymore.

11
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:13,907
I think this is
where we should end it, Father.

12
00:01:14,616 --> 00:01:15,908
Listen.

13
00:01:15,909 --> 00:01:17,911
I know how you feel.

14
00:01:19,705 --> 00:01:23,000
You see, that's just how life is.

15
00:01:23,959 --> 00:01:24,960
Taeju.

16
00:01:25,877 --> 00:01:27,546
Do you think I've never felt that way?

17
00:01:28,589 --> 00:01:29,881
I've been there.

18
00:01:30,882 --> 00:01:33,135
I wanted to give it all up and run away.

19
00:01:34,970 --> 00:01:37,014
But I had a family to protect.

20
00:01:38,557 --> 00:01:40,350
I just had to suck it up.

21
00:01:42,102 --> 00:01:44,479
That's how I kept myself going.

22
00:01:59,578 --> 00:02:00,704
Your heart,

23
00:02:02,247 --> 00:02:04,041
your values, your morals…

24
00:02:05,917 --> 00:02:07,294
Just put them all aside.

25
00:02:11,256 --> 00:02:13,008
Don't let Seyun see them.

26
00:02:14,384 --> 00:02:18,889
It'd only hurt her, all right?

27
00:02:26,271 --> 00:02:28,106
EPISODE 5

28
00:02:47,834 --> 00:02:50,212
BEHAVIORAL HEALTH
CONSULTATION ROOM

29
00:03:13,485 --> 00:03:14,861
Come on in, Taeju.

30
00:03:24,454 --> 00:03:25,455
Are you okay?

31
00:03:27,624 --> 00:03:29,292
No.

32
00:03:34,506 --> 00:03:37,134
Sounds like the talk didn't go well.

33
00:03:52,858 --> 00:03:54,776
It's okay. It happens.

34
00:04:07,747 --> 00:04:09,498
It's okay, Taeju.

35
00:04:14,546 --> 00:04:15,547
Don't you worry.

36
00:04:16,715 --> 00:04:18,049
This isn't the end.

37
00:04:26,433 --> 00:04:31,354
THE HUSBAND

38
00:04:44,242 --> 00:04:45,410
Where are we?

39
00:04:48,622 --> 00:04:50,165
I thought we were going to my wife.

40
00:04:50,665 --> 00:04:53,210
That's for you
to figure out from here on out.

41
00:04:56,338 --> 00:05:00,049
It's the exact same MO
as my wife's murder six years ago.

42
00:05:02,010 --> 00:05:03,886
ESTIMATED TOD
36-37 HRS AFTER RANSOM CALL

43
00:05:03,887 --> 00:05:10,227
His window for murder is
36 to 38 hours post-ransom call.

44
00:05:11,186 --> 00:05:15,190
It's already been 15 hours
since he took your wife.

45
00:05:16,566 --> 00:05:18,485
Your wife is still alive.

46
00:05:19,653 --> 00:05:21,363
Though she doesn't have much time left.

47
00:05:21,947 --> 00:05:23,490
So what do I have to do now

48
00:05:24,115 --> 00:05:25,367
to save my wife?

49
00:05:26,827 --> 00:05:27,869
To pick up the money.

50
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:29,955
What? Money?

51
00:05:30,455 --> 00:05:35,376
The three billion you have here.
I need you to hand it over to me.

52
00:05:35,377 --> 00:05:38,420
Let Seyun go first.
Then I'll give you the money.

53
00:05:38,421 --> 00:05:40,089
No, Mother.

54
00:05:40,090 --> 00:05:42,925
Give me the money first.
That's the only way she'll live.

55
00:05:42,926 --> 00:05:44,510
What?

56
00:05:44,511 --> 00:05:45,762
You greedy bastard!

57
00:05:49,599 --> 00:05:50,642
Just take it!

58
00:05:51,476 --> 00:05:53,186
Please, just take the money!

59
00:06:14,583 --> 00:06:16,334
You made it onto the news.

60
00:06:19,462 --> 00:06:21,006
The culprit must've seen it too.

61
00:06:23,592 --> 00:06:26,052
CHOI HYEONSU
NATIONAL POLICE AGENCY

62
00:06:27,721 --> 00:06:29,013
The NFS?

63
00:06:29,014 --> 00:06:31,224
You want me to go there? Why?

64
00:06:31,725 --> 00:06:33,642
To find the bait to lure him out.

65
00:06:33,643 --> 00:06:35,604
REVEALING THE TRUTH
WITH THE POWER OF SCIENCE

66
00:06:44,446 --> 00:06:45,739
SEOUL SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

67
00:06:46,281 --> 00:06:48,617
URGENT RETRIEVAL OF THE ABOVE
FORENSIC EVIDENCE ITEMS

68
00:06:51,369 --> 00:06:55,331
Hi, I'm with Seongjin Police.
I'm here to urgently collect the evidence.

69
00:06:55,332 --> 00:06:57,125
Okay, give me a moment.

70
00:07:35,413 --> 00:07:38,248
How are we supposed to use
surveillance cameras to contact him?

71
00:07:38,249 --> 00:07:39,583
KIDNAPPING OF KO SEYUN

72
00:07:45,632 --> 00:07:48,509
145-138 SONGLIM-DONG

73
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:51,929
CAMERA POSITION AT THE TIME
OF INITIAL DISCOVERY NEAR ENTRYWAY

74
00:07:51,930 --> 00:07:54,474
The detectives found them
at your in-laws'.

75
00:08:10,615 --> 00:08:12,074
Captain!

76
00:08:12,075 --> 00:08:13,159
Over here.

77
00:08:19,541 --> 00:08:20,625
Take a look.

78
00:08:25,463 --> 00:08:26,464
Detective.

79
00:08:27,632 --> 00:08:29,759
They found cameras at your house too.

80
00:08:34,597 --> 00:08:35,724
Over here!

81
00:08:39,144 --> 00:08:42,105
And these cameras were found
during a follow-up search.

82
00:08:45,191 --> 00:08:46,526
He's been…

83
00:08:49,612 --> 00:08:51,448
watching you all along.

84
00:10:11,694 --> 00:10:14,613
What on earth is this guy doing? Geez…

85
00:10:21,371 --> 00:10:22,372
Hmm?

86
00:11:14,048 --> 00:11:15,884
UNKNOWN NUMBER

87
00:11:20,305 --> 00:11:21,431
Hello?

88
00:11:23,141 --> 00:11:24,642
It's been a while, Mr. Kang.

89
00:11:25,852 --> 00:11:28,271
I thought I'd never see you again,
but here you are.

90
00:11:29,105 --> 00:11:31,149
Can we skip the pleasantries?

91
00:11:33,234 --> 00:11:35,319
You've gotten real famous in the meantime.

92
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:37,571
I wasn't sure
it was the same Mr. Kang I knew.

93
00:11:37,572 --> 00:11:39,574
I'm honestly surprised.

94
00:11:40,408 --> 00:11:41,659
And my wife?

95
00:11:44,537 --> 00:11:45,788
Where is she?

96
00:11:51,044 --> 00:11:52,045
She is…

97
00:11:54,881 --> 00:11:56,257
still alive, right?

98
00:12:03,973 --> 00:12:05,016
For now, yes.

99
00:12:10,230 --> 00:12:12,065
Just out of genuine curiosity…

100
00:12:14,442 --> 00:12:16,236
Why are you really doing this to us?

101
00:12:17,779 --> 00:12:20,864
You asked me for a favor, and I delivered.

102
00:12:20,865 --> 00:12:22,408
So what kind of question is that?

103
00:12:23,117 --> 00:12:25,036
What am I even supposed to say?

104
00:12:25,828 --> 00:12:28,872
No. Cut the crap already.

105
00:12:28,873 --> 00:12:31,125
Why are you really doing this to us?

106
00:12:31,751 --> 00:12:32,752
Listen, boss.

107
00:12:33,419 --> 00:12:35,922
That shouldn't even matter
to you right now.

108
00:12:36,673 --> 00:12:40,467
What should matter is
that your wife is going to die,

109
00:12:40,468 --> 00:12:44,347
and you're going to have to live
with the guilt for the rest of your life.

110
00:13:23,303 --> 00:13:24,637
Here's your money as promised.

111
00:13:28,474 --> 00:13:30,059
For real this time.

112
00:13:38,901 --> 00:13:41,821
Mr. Kang, it's already over.

113
00:13:42,488 --> 00:13:43,740
It's too late.

114
00:13:45,116 --> 00:13:47,160
How does Hogok Park in three hours sound?

115
00:13:50,204 --> 00:13:51,706
Did you not hear me?

116
00:13:59,839 --> 00:14:00,923
Is this funny?

117
00:14:01,841 --> 00:14:03,384
Yeah, it is.

118
00:14:04,844 --> 00:14:07,346
You knew it was me
when you accessed this camera.

119
00:14:08,848 --> 00:14:09,974
Why did you even call me?

120
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:12,894
Did you just want to hear my voice?

121
00:14:15,646 --> 00:14:17,315
You do want the money, don't you?

122
00:14:20,568 --> 00:14:22,612
Three billion won in cash.

123
00:14:23,905 --> 00:14:25,989
It's not mixed in
with 1,000-won bills either.

124
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:27,617
This is the real deal.

125
00:14:30,119 --> 00:14:31,829
You're saying you don't want it, right?

126
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:57,396
I might as well destroy it then.

127
00:15:02,235 --> 00:15:04,403
Okay. Fine.

128
00:15:05,238 --> 00:15:07,615
You've gotten pretty smart, Mr. Kang.

129
00:15:08,950 --> 00:15:10,201
All right.

130
00:15:10,993 --> 00:15:13,078
Why don't we talk this out?

131
00:15:13,079 --> 00:15:15,456
Yeah, I'd love to.

132
00:15:16,124 --> 00:15:17,125
But first,

133
00:15:18,084 --> 00:15:20,711
I need to confirm my wife is alive.

134
00:15:21,963 --> 00:15:23,464
Put her on the phone.

135
00:17:13,199 --> 00:17:14,200
Come on.

136
00:17:15,117 --> 00:17:17,161
Come on, please.

137
00:18:27,398 --> 00:18:28,691
Stay away from me.

138
00:18:31,777 --> 00:18:32,986
I said, stay away!

139
00:18:32,987 --> 00:18:34,280
It's for you.

140
00:18:37,366 --> 00:18:39,702
I said it's for you.
You don't want to take the call?

141
00:18:41,537 --> 00:18:43,706
Not again.

142
00:18:44,415 --> 00:18:46,626
I keep forgetting I tied up your hands.

143
00:18:47,793 --> 00:18:50,338
This is your fault for trying to escape!

144
00:18:53,966 --> 00:18:56,135
Just talk like this. Okay?

145
00:18:59,305 --> 00:19:00,306
It's your husband.

146
00:19:02,892 --> 00:19:03,976
My husband?

147
00:19:05,019 --> 00:19:06,062
Hello?

148
00:19:06,646 --> 00:19:07,647
Seyun.

149
00:19:09,065 --> 00:19:10,148
Seyun?

150
00:19:13,611 --> 00:19:14,778
Is that really you?

151
00:19:14,779 --> 00:19:16,364
Yes, honey. It's me.

152
00:19:17,657 --> 00:19:18,658
Are you okay?

153
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:20,451
Are you hurt anywhere?

154
00:19:25,414 --> 00:19:26,832
Yeah, I'm fine.

155
00:19:30,670 --> 00:19:32,171
Okay, thank goodness.

156
00:19:34,340 --> 00:19:35,341
Honey.

157
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:39,970
I'm sorry. About everything.

158
00:19:41,263 --> 00:19:42,764
No, honey.

159
00:19:42,765 --> 00:19:45,851
No, really. I really am sorry.

160
00:19:46,727 --> 00:19:48,813
About so many different things.

161
00:19:49,522 --> 00:19:53,901
I've had so much
I've wanted to say to you.

162
00:19:54,652 --> 00:19:57,530
I don't know why
I've been putting it all off.

163
00:19:59,073 --> 00:20:00,949
Let's talk in person, okay?

164
00:20:00,950 --> 00:20:04,035
I'm coming for you. Just hang in there.

165
00:20:04,036 --> 00:20:05,037
Okay?

166
00:20:05,913 --> 00:20:06,997
Yeah.

167
00:20:07,873 --> 00:20:09,500
I'll be waiting for you.

168
00:20:10,126 --> 00:20:11,835
You're testing my patience, man.

169
00:20:11,836 --> 00:20:12,919
Honey.

170
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:14,505
Okay, that's enough, right?

171
00:20:15,131 --> 00:20:17,591
All right, shall we
get back to our deal now?

172
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:22,847
You know, I've been thinking about it.

173
00:20:24,515 --> 00:20:27,727
Why do you get to decide the location?
I'm the one holding the hostage.

174
00:20:28,936 --> 00:20:29,937
Okay.

175
00:20:32,022 --> 00:20:33,607
Go ahead. Pick one.

176
00:20:34,692 --> 00:20:37,778
At 8 p.m. tonight,
wait in front of Dong Nam Sports Center.

177
00:20:38,863 --> 00:20:41,741
I'll tell you the exact location then.

178
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:45,702
This time, make sure you bring the money.

179
00:20:59,633 --> 00:21:00,926
Is the scar any better yet?

180
00:21:01,427 --> 00:21:03,595
Hey, come on. Just stay still.

181
00:21:06,140 --> 00:21:07,141
Come on!

182
00:21:10,311 --> 00:21:11,603
Looks all right.

183
00:21:13,981 --> 00:21:15,274
Ms. Ko.

184
00:21:16,692 --> 00:21:17,985
About Mr. Kang.

185
00:21:18,778 --> 00:21:20,112
Is he always this flaky?

186
00:21:22,281 --> 00:21:26,951
I mean, at first, he wanted you dead,
and now, he wants me to let you live.

187
00:21:26,952 --> 00:21:30,873
I don't know what he wants anymore.
It's so exhausting.

188
00:21:31,415 --> 00:21:32,666
What are you talking about?

189
00:21:34,251 --> 00:21:35,335
He wanted me dead?

190
00:21:35,336 --> 00:21:36,878
Oh.

191
00:21:36,879 --> 00:21:38,589
I guess you didn't know.

192
00:21:39,673 --> 00:21:41,759
Ugh, should I tell you this or not?

193
00:21:46,722 --> 00:21:47,848
Ms. Ko.

194
00:21:48,766 --> 00:21:50,850
Mr. Kang put me up to all this.

195
00:21:53,395 --> 00:21:54,772
Don't you lie to me.

196
00:21:58,776 --> 00:21:59,777
I'm not.

197
00:22:00,694 --> 00:22:02,320
He'd never do something like that.

198
00:22:02,321 --> 00:22:05,491
I heard he asked for a divorce,
but you said no.

199
00:22:06,075 --> 00:22:08,744
That you didn't want to
give him anything he wanted.

200
00:22:13,249 --> 00:22:15,417
I'm sure that's what he told me.

201
00:22:17,086 --> 00:22:18,254
Did he not?

202
00:22:44,113 --> 00:22:45,781
NAMGANG LIVESTOCK DISTRIBUTION

203
00:22:53,497 --> 00:22:55,332
It's the black sedan out front.

204
00:22:57,418 --> 00:23:00,421
When he calls,
he'll tell you the exact location.

205
00:23:01,297 --> 00:23:04,466
Don't get worked up, and be cooperative.

206
00:23:05,175 --> 00:23:07,886
Until you know for sure
that your wife is safe,

207
00:23:07,887 --> 00:23:09,178
don't do anything rash.

208
00:23:09,179 --> 00:23:11,473
Don't react to him. Just wait.

209
00:23:13,350 --> 00:23:15,311
That's the only way
you can save your wife.

210
00:23:17,021 --> 00:23:18,354
I understand.

211
00:23:18,355 --> 00:23:19,607
Good.

212
00:23:31,911 --> 00:23:35,163
I'll be watching from a distance
just in case anything happens.

213
00:23:35,164 --> 00:23:38,791
When he takes the money and releases
your wife as per the agreement,

214
00:23:38,792 --> 00:23:40,544
leave with her immediately.

215
00:23:43,797 --> 00:23:45,174
And don't look back.

216
00:23:47,885 --> 00:23:50,554
Once you're clear, I'll handle the rest.

217
00:23:55,809 --> 00:23:58,227
Remember, this is just a last resort.

218
00:23:58,228 --> 00:24:02,316
Use it at the wrong time,
and you may never see your wife again.

219
00:24:17,790 --> 00:24:20,960
DONG NAM SPORTS CENTER

220
00:25:14,763 --> 00:25:16,015
Where do I meet you?

221
00:25:16,974 --> 00:25:17,975
Mr. Kang.

222
00:25:18,892 --> 00:25:20,769
Come to Do San Development Company.

223
00:25:21,270 --> 00:25:22,354
You have 10 minutes.

224
00:25:30,446 --> 00:25:31,947
I'm heading to Do San Development.

225
00:25:32,656 --> 00:25:34,282
I only have 10 minutes.

226
00:25:34,283 --> 00:25:36,618
Stay calm and stick to the plan.

227
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:39,328
Okay.

228
00:25:39,329 --> 00:25:41,373
"Stay calm and stick to the plan."

229
00:25:42,249 --> 00:25:43,876
Your wife can be saved.

230
00:25:45,544 --> 00:25:46,712
Don't worry.

231
00:26:24,249 --> 00:26:25,751
DO SAN DEVELOPMENT COMPANY

232
00:26:27,795 --> 00:26:30,255
Up ahead,
make a left turn at nine o'clock.

233
00:26:45,229 --> 00:26:46,355
Keep driving.

234
00:26:46,855 --> 00:26:48,941
You'll see an open lot
next to the machinery.

235
00:26:49,733 --> 00:26:50,943
Wait for me there.

236
00:27:04,373 --> 00:27:05,791
What do you see?

237
00:27:06,792 --> 00:27:08,710
I don't see anything yet.

238
00:27:14,716 --> 00:27:16,426
Stay on your toes.

239
00:28:47,100 --> 00:28:48,185
What are you doing?

240
00:28:51,521 --> 00:28:52,981
No!

241
00:28:54,900 --> 00:28:56,318
No!

242
00:28:59,237 --> 00:29:00,571
Stop it!

243
00:29:00,572 --> 00:29:02,073
What the hell are you doing?

244
00:29:02,074 --> 00:29:04,910
Let go!

245
00:29:14,711 --> 00:29:16,046
Seyun!

246
00:29:25,055 --> 00:29:26,056
Stop the car!

247
00:29:26,890 --> 00:29:27,891
Stop the car.

248
00:29:29,601 --> 00:29:31,728
Get out!

249
00:29:37,734 --> 00:29:38,818
You!

250
00:29:42,739 --> 00:29:44,281
Seyun.

251
00:29:44,282 --> 00:29:47,702
Seyun!

252
00:29:47,703 --> 00:29:50,162
Seyun!

253
00:29:50,163 --> 00:29:52,540
Seyun!

254
00:29:52,541 --> 00:29:55,252
It was you, you bastard. Die.

255
00:29:56,086 --> 00:29:57,878
- Die!
-  Hey, Park. What's going on?

256
00:29:57,879 --> 00:29:59,714
I heard gunshots. What was that?

257
00:29:59,715 --> 00:30:01,632
Jeongu! Answer me now!

258
00:30:01,633 --> 00:30:03,343
PARK JEONGU
NATIONAL POLICE AGENCY

259
00:30:04,469 --> 00:30:05,470
No.

260
00:30:06,221 --> 00:30:07,222
No!

261
00:30:07,848 --> 00:30:10,017
No, you can't kill him!

262
00:30:10,559 --> 00:30:13,645
He's a police officer!
Get a hold of yourself!

263
00:30:14,688 --> 00:30:17,023
He's a cop.

264
00:30:19,860 --> 00:30:21,111
Get out of here!

265
00:31:22,881 --> 00:31:24,466
- Hurry!
- Over there! Go!

266
00:31:26,218 --> 00:31:29,012
Over there! Move it!

267
00:31:34,601 --> 00:31:36,144
Stop right there!

268
00:31:37,437 --> 00:31:38,480
Stop, Kang Taeju!

269
00:31:40,816 --> 00:31:42,526
-  Stop right there!
-  Kang Taeju, stop!

270
00:31:43,693 --> 00:31:45,904
- Damn it. You bastard.
- Kang Taeju!

271
00:31:46,404 --> 00:31:48,573
-  You prick!
-  Kang Taeju!

272
00:31:50,659 --> 00:31:52,035
LAW ENFORCEMENT

273
00:31:56,039 --> 00:31:57,873
- Kang Taeju!
-  Stop right there!

274
00:31:57,874 --> 00:31:59,376
Hey!

275
00:32:01,294 --> 00:32:03,379
Go get him! Get him!

276
00:32:03,380 --> 00:32:05,047
Kang Taeju!

277
00:32:05,048 --> 00:32:07,342
- Kang Taeju, I said stop!
-  Stop right there, punk!

278
00:32:11,930 --> 00:32:15,767
Kang Taeju, stop!

279
00:32:18,979 --> 00:32:21,064
Hey, don't be reckless!

280
00:32:34,870 --> 00:32:36,413
Kang Taeju!

281
00:32:41,209 --> 00:32:42,460
It's dangerous!

282
00:32:51,261 --> 00:32:53,096
- Go that way!
- Yes, sir!

283
00:33:00,437 --> 00:33:01,854
Damn it!

284
00:33:01,855 --> 00:33:02,856
Kang Taeju!

285
00:33:03,481 --> 00:33:05,441
Drop your weapon and surrender!

286
00:33:07,152 --> 00:33:10,197
Don't come close!

287
00:33:11,406 --> 00:33:12,824
Stay away.

288
00:33:15,368 --> 00:33:16,493
Get in the car!

289
00:33:18,538 --> 00:33:21,499
Kang Taeju, calm down. Drop the weapon!

290
00:33:35,263 --> 00:33:36,556
Kang Taeju!

291
00:33:37,766 --> 00:33:39,059
-  Crap!
-  Kang Taeju!

292
00:33:40,268 --> 00:33:41,477
Damn it.

293
00:33:41,478 --> 00:33:43,646
Get in the car and go after them!

294
00:33:43,647 --> 00:33:44,814
- Get going!
- Yes, sir.

295
00:33:51,696 --> 00:33:52,697
Ms. Ko.

296
00:33:53,490 --> 00:33:56,868
Mr. Kang put me up to all this.

297
00:33:57,911 --> 00:34:00,664
I heard he asked for a divorce,
but you said no.

298
00:34:01,790 --> 00:34:04,167
That you didn't want to
give him anything he wanted.

299
00:34:06,962 --> 00:34:08,045
No way.

300
00:34:09,422 --> 00:34:11,508
It can't be.

301
00:34:16,721 --> 00:34:18,306
There's not much time.

302
00:34:42,247 --> 00:34:43,707
What was that about?

303
00:34:44,207 --> 00:34:46,459
What if it was my wife
in that car back there?

304
00:34:48,795 --> 00:34:50,004
Answer me!

305
00:34:50,005 --> 00:34:52,507
What if she was in that car?

306
00:34:53,049 --> 00:34:54,843
You could have killed her right there!

307
00:34:55,844 --> 00:34:57,804
I knew she wasn't going to be there.

308
00:34:58,638 --> 00:35:00,139
What?

309
00:35:00,140 --> 00:35:01,349
What are you talking about?

310
00:35:06,563 --> 00:35:07,564
Get off me!

311
00:35:08,940 --> 00:35:10,734
- Detective Lee!
- Get off!

312
00:35:11,234 --> 00:35:12,402
I said get off me!

313
00:35:13,320 --> 00:35:14,778
- You can't!
- Who is it? Hey!

314
00:35:14,779 --> 00:35:16,572
Please! You can't, Detective Lee!

315
00:35:16,573 --> 00:35:17,990
You can't go in!

316
00:35:17,991 --> 00:35:20,534
- I said no!
- Let go of me! Let go!

317
00:35:28,418 --> 00:35:30,503
- Gyeongmin!
- Grab him!

318
00:35:31,546 --> 00:35:32,881
Gyeongmin!

319
00:35:33,381 --> 00:35:34,382
Gyeongmin!

320
00:35:37,719 --> 00:35:41,514
She had been dead for at least two hours
before the time he had agreed on with you.

321
00:35:42,641 --> 00:35:45,018
ESTIMATED TOD
36-37 HRS AFTER INITIAL RANSOM CALL

322
00:35:46,978 --> 00:35:48,188
My wife

323
00:35:49,105 --> 00:35:52,192
was already dead by the time
I was supposed to meet the culprit.

324
00:35:53,193 --> 00:35:55,487
Even if I'd taken the money he wanted,

325
00:35:56,154 --> 00:35:59,032
he was never going to let her live.

326
00:36:00,617 --> 00:36:02,744
You think it's different this time?

327
00:36:05,538 --> 00:36:07,082
But why did the police come here?

328
00:36:07,916 --> 00:36:09,668
How did they know to be there?

329
00:36:10,752 --> 00:36:12,128
Who tipped them off?

330
00:36:14,047 --> 00:36:15,048
Stop the car.

331
00:36:15,924 --> 00:36:17,217
Stop the car right now!

332
00:36:23,723 --> 00:36:24,724
You…

333
00:36:27,852 --> 00:36:30,230
You never meant to save my wife, did you?

334
00:36:38,738 --> 00:36:41,240
This is just about revenge, isn't it?

335
00:36:41,241 --> 00:36:43,034
Is that really important?

336
00:36:43,702 --> 00:36:45,870
We walked into the bastard's trap.

337
00:36:47,288 --> 00:36:48,832
I almost had him.

338
00:36:50,542 --> 00:36:52,668
I almost had him this time.

339
00:36:52,669 --> 00:36:54,337
And my wife?

340
00:36:54,879 --> 00:36:56,256
What about my wife?

341
00:36:56,756 --> 00:36:58,216
What about my wife?

342
00:36:58,842 --> 00:36:59,843
You're right.

343
00:37:01,594 --> 00:37:03,221
It's just about revenge.

344
00:37:04,931 --> 00:37:05,932
So what?

345
00:37:07,517 --> 00:37:08,518
What's wrong with that?

346
00:37:12,814 --> 00:37:13,815
You…

347
00:37:15,275 --> 00:37:17,861
You just disgust me.

348
00:37:18,361 --> 00:37:19,571
What of it?

349
00:37:20,822 --> 00:37:22,407
What's wrong with that?

350
00:37:23,366 --> 00:37:24,367
Shoot me.

351
00:37:25,076 --> 00:37:26,453
Just do it!

352
00:37:49,184 --> 00:37:50,185
Taeju!

353
00:38:02,697 --> 00:38:03,864
Kang Taeju.

354
00:38:20,507 --> 00:38:21,508
Hey, Mr. Lee Suhyeong!

355
00:38:22,008 --> 00:38:23,301
Are you okay?

356
00:38:24,719 --> 00:38:25,720
Look at me!

357
00:38:45,365 --> 00:38:46,991
This is the end of our deal.

358
00:38:52,747 --> 00:38:55,792
You can consider your wife dead now.

359
00:39:00,463 --> 00:39:02,131
No!

360
00:39:04,425 --> 00:39:05,801
No!

361
00:39:05,802 --> 00:39:08,054
No.

362
00:39:28,324 --> 00:39:30,909
Mr. Lee. Don't talk.

363
00:39:30,910 --> 00:39:32,745
Just hang in there, okay?

364
00:39:34,747 --> 00:39:37,791
- I…
-  Hello? What's your emergency?

365
00:39:37,792 --> 00:39:39,919
- I'm sorry.
- Hello?

366
00:39:40,712 --> 00:39:42,713
-  Save her.
- Hello?

367
00:39:42,714 --> 00:39:45,300
You have to save your wife.

368
00:39:51,014 --> 00:39:54,099
No!

369
00:39:54,100 --> 00:39:55,476
No! Please.

370
00:39:56,144 --> 00:39:57,896
Hey! Mr. Lee Suhyeong!

371
00:39:58,980 --> 00:40:00,273
No!

372
00:40:51,824 --> 00:40:53,075
Where do I meet you?

373
00:40:56,871 --> 00:40:57,872
Mr. Kang.

374
00:40:58,706 --> 00:41:00,333
Come to Do San Development Company.

375
00:41:01,250 --> 00:41:02,585
You have 10 minutes.

376
00:41:36,077 --> 00:41:37,078
Look who it is.

377
00:41:42,625 --> 00:41:43,626
Uh…

378
00:41:46,129 --> 00:41:47,130
That's how it is?

379
00:42:00,143 --> 00:42:01,269
Is this the police?

380
00:42:02,020 --> 00:42:04,939
It's as if you're begging me to kill her.

381
00:42:06,107 --> 00:42:08,275
Wait, what was the guy's name?

382
00:42:08,276 --> 00:42:11,319
Whatever, he's already dead anyway.

383
00:42:11,320 --> 00:42:13,155
What matters is the three billion won!

384
00:42:13,156 --> 00:42:15,240
I almost had it!

385
00:42:17,118 --> 00:42:18,619
Kang Taeju, you prick.

386
00:42:19,203 --> 00:42:20,496
Just you wait.

387
00:42:21,664 --> 00:42:24,584
I'm going to make sure
she dies a slow, painful death.

388
00:42:43,853 --> 00:42:46,229
What did I ever do wrong?

389
00:42:48,608 --> 00:42:50,860
Why is this happening to me?

390
00:43:55,007 --> 00:43:56,008
Captain.

391
00:43:56,676 --> 00:43:57,677
Yeah.

392
00:43:58,177 --> 00:44:00,304
Have a look. This is an illegal firearm.

393
00:44:00,847 --> 00:44:02,515
The serial number's been filed off.

394
00:44:04,433 --> 00:44:06,977
Oh, right. The hospital called.

395
00:44:06,978 --> 00:44:11,607
Park hasn't regained consciousness,
but they said he'll live.

396
00:44:12,650 --> 00:44:15,403
Oh, and here.
We found it in Kang's vehicle.

397
00:44:21,659 --> 00:44:22,869
I don't get it.

398
00:44:23,911 --> 00:44:26,621
I mean, he's wanted for solicitation.

399
00:44:26,622 --> 00:44:29,082
Since he took the money from his in-laws,

400
00:44:29,083 --> 00:44:30,668
you'd expect him to go off the grid.

401
00:44:32,295 --> 00:44:36,549
But instead, he stole evidence
from the NFS with a fake ID,

402
00:44:37,216 --> 00:44:39,343
and he came here
with an illegal firearm.

403
00:44:41,512 --> 00:44:43,848
What was he planning to do here?

404
00:44:45,683 --> 00:44:49,145
Also, who's the guy he was with?

405
00:44:52,982 --> 00:44:54,442
Trace the gun's origin.

406
00:44:55,026 --> 00:44:56,902
Run a DNA analysis on this blood sample.

407
00:44:56,903 --> 00:44:58,236
I'm on it.

408
00:45:04,160 --> 00:45:05,161
Yes, talk.

409
00:45:05,870 --> 00:45:07,038
What?

410
00:45:07,622 --> 00:45:08,830
Where?

411
00:45:08,831 --> 00:45:11,082
EMERGENCY SERVICES, AMBULANCE

412
00:45:23,971 --> 00:45:25,514
- Detective Oh.
- Yeah, Captain.

413
00:45:26,641 --> 00:45:28,850
What happened here? Where's Kang Taeju?

414
00:45:28,851 --> 00:45:32,104
He wasn't here. The crash victim
was just sent to the hospital.

415
00:45:32,939 --> 00:45:36,691
There are no skid marks.
Looks like it was deliberate.

416
00:45:36,692 --> 00:45:38,027
Did you ID the victim?

417
00:45:38,611 --> 00:45:41,155
His name is Lee Suhyeong.
He used to be a detective.

418
00:45:42,240 --> 00:45:43,241
Lee Suhyeong?

419
00:45:44,367 --> 00:45:45,659
Why does it ring a bell?

420
00:45:45,660 --> 00:45:48,828
His wife was kidnapped
and murdered a few years back.

421
00:45:48,829 --> 00:45:51,290
He went rogue,
was suspended, and then retired.

422
00:45:52,124 --> 00:45:54,377
- Right, from Dongin PD?
- Yes, sir.

423
00:45:57,505 --> 00:45:58,630
Who called it in?

424
00:45:58,631 --> 00:46:01,716
We couldn't get an ID.
The call was from a burner phone.

425
00:46:01,717 --> 00:46:03,094
And it was a bit unusual.

426
00:46:03,594 --> 00:46:06,638
The caller said the victim
had chest trauma and internal bleeding

427
00:46:06,639 --> 00:46:07,847
due to the crash,

428
00:46:07,848 --> 00:46:09,975
and then claimed
that the crash was deliberate.

429
00:46:09,976 --> 00:46:12,520
He requested that an ambulance
and police be dispatched.

430
00:46:14,230 --> 00:46:16,607
Captain, could it have been Kang Taeju?

431
00:46:17,316 --> 00:46:19,234
Could he also have crashed
into Lee Suhyeong?

432
00:46:19,235 --> 00:46:22,445
We can't be sure yet, but he's certainly
got something to do with it.

433
00:46:22,446 --> 00:46:25,366
Detective Oh, we got the address.

434
00:46:26,033 --> 00:46:27,951
We've got the address for Lee's residence.

435
00:46:27,952 --> 00:46:29,287
Where is it?

436
00:46:44,677 --> 00:46:46,387
This is the end of our deal.

437
00:46:48,014 --> 00:46:50,933
You can consider your wife dead now.

438
00:46:51,517 --> 00:46:52,685
My wife

439
00:46:53,936 --> 00:46:57,023
was already dead by the time
I was supposed to meet the culprit.

440
00:46:58,190 --> 00:47:01,027
He was never going to let her live.

441
00:47:02,653 --> 00:47:04,864
You think it's different this time?

442
00:48:00,086 --> 00:48:01,420
PARK GYEONGMIN

443
00:48:14,642 --> 00:48:16,810
VICTIM'S SHIRT BUTTON
INTENTIONALLY REMOVED

444
00:48:16,811 --> 00:48:18,437
EVIDENCE NO. 2
FEBRUARY 1, 2020

445
00:48:25,277 --> 00:48:26,695
Okay, thank you.

446
00:48:34,870 --> 00:48:37,665
NAMGANG LIVESTOCK DISTRIBUTION

447
00:49:05,151 --> 00:49:06,277
Captain!

448
00:49:27,006 --> 00:49:28,756
NEUROSURGEON KANG TAEJU

449
00:49:28,757 --> 00:49:29,800
SEYUN

450
00:51:24,540 --> 00:51:26,791
STAIRWELL
FIRE DOOR, KEEP CLOSED

451
00:51:26,792 --> 00:51:29,795
DO NOT PLACE OBJECTS
NEAR FIRE DOOR

452
00:51:49,982 --> 00:51:52,942
HEALTH CARE CENTER

453
00:53:08,227 --> 00:53:09,728
WOORI TOGETHER MEDICAL CENTER

454
00:53:18,320 --> 00:53:22,157
LOGIN
KTJ0630

455
00:53:55,232 --> 00:53:56,233
Ms. Ko!

456
00:53:57,860 --> 00:53:59,111
Ms. Ko!

457
00:54:04,575 --> 00:54:07,411
Ms. Ko, it's all over!

458
00:54:21,508 --> 00:54:22,509
What are you doing?

459
00:54:28,599 --> 00:54:29,933
Damn it!

460
00:54:37,232 --> 00:54:40,068
What the hell is wrong with you?

461
00:54:53,707 --> 00:54:54,708
Goddamnit!

462
00:55:15,646 --> 00:55:17,021
Last month…

463
00:55:17,022 --> 00:55:19,524
PATIENT FILES
JANUARY 2026

464
00:55:19,525 --> 00:55:20,526
APPLY

465
00:55:33,580 --> 00:55:37,250
Okay, so what seems to be the problem?

466
00:55:37,251 --> 00:55:39,502
My legs have been a little numb.

467
00:55:39,503 --> 00:55:43,297
My thighs feel tight, and they tingle
like they're being shocked.

468
00:55:46,510 --> 00:55:48,678
"Male."

469
00:55:48,679 --> 00:55:50,513
MALE

470
00:55:50,514 --> 00:55:51,515
APPLY

471
00:55:53,850 --> 00:55:57,312
So, these symptoms mainly happen
when you're walking, right?

472
00:55:58,313 --> 00:56:01,774
Yeah. Well, not exactly all the time, but…

473
00:56:01,775 --> 00:56:04,152
"In his forties."

474
00:56:05,487 --> 00:56:07,905
40S

475
00:56:07,906 --> 00:56:10,284
APPLY

476
00:56:21,545 --> 00:56:26,674
"Ma Seongyeon,
nerve root compression."

477
00:56:26,675 --> 00:56:28,844
"Kim Duchan,

478
00:56:30,387 --> 00:56:33,139
dorsum foot pain."

479
00:56:33,140 --> 00:56:34,725
"Heo Jaeil…"

480
00:56:36,143 --> 00:56:38,979
"Feels like legs are being shocked…"

481
00:56:39,855 --> 00:56:42,774
"Radiating pain in both legs."

482
00:56:45,902 --> 00:56:49,114
"Intermittent neurogenic claudication."

483
00:56:51,199 --> 00:56:52,450
TINGLING SENSATION IN LEGS

484
00:56:52,451 --> 00:56:54,411
INTERMITTENT NEUROGENIC CLAUDICATION

485
00:56:55,162 --> 00:56:57,496
I'll write you a prescription
for about two weeks,

486
00:56:57,497 --> 00:56:59,082
and let's see how you feel by then.

487
00:57:01,793 --> 00:57:02,961
Okay, thank you.

488
00:57:41,041 --> 00:57:43,793
BUTTON

489
00:57:50,008 --> 00:57:54,805
BUTTON

490
00:58:02,562 --> 00:58:04,314
What the hell?

491
00:58:09,569 --> 00:58:10,570
Ms. Ko!

492
00:58:19,996 --> 00:58:21,164
"Heo Jaeil."

493
00:58:23,375 --> 00:58:25,126
"47-3, Yongho 3-gil."

494
00:58:25,127 --> 00:58:27,379
47-3, YONGHO 3-GIL,
ILWON-MYEON, YEOCHEON-SI

495
00:58:38,098 --> 00:58:39,307
Found you.

496
00:58:42,686 --> 00:58:47,606
THE HUSBAND

497
00:59:28,607 --> 00:59:29,982
Where are you going?

498
00:59:29,983 --> 00:59:31,735
Ms. Ko!

499
00:59:32,277 --> 00:59:34,195
I'm looking for her right now.

500
00:59:34,196 --> 00:59:35,821
I'm going to bring Seyun home.

501
00:59:35,822 --> 00:59:38,240
Ms. Ko, I'm not mad yet. Okay?

502
00:59:38,241 --> 00:59:40,952
But if you keep this up,
I'm going to get really mad!

503
00:59:42,120 --> 00:59:43,871
Seyun…

504
00:59:43,872 --> 00:59:45,832
Help me! Please!

505
00:59:46,750 --> 00:59:48,042
Please help me.

506
00:59:48,043 --> 00:59:49,126
What's going on?

507
00:59:49,127 --> 00:59:52,296
It really is a scary world out there.

508
00:59:52,297 --> 00:59:54,548
How could someone do such a thing?

509
00:59:54,549 --> 00:59:55,508
Mr. Kang?

510
00:59:55,509 --> 00:59:57,593
Manhui, I finally got your name.

511
00:59:57,594 --> 00:59:59,513
Talk. Where is my wife?

512
01:00:00,472 --> 01:00:02,474
Translated by Hyun Sik Yoon
